itemLabel: John St Aubyn, 4th Baron Saint Levan

wikipedia_page.main: John Francis Arthur St Aubyn, 4th Baron St Levan OBE DSC DL  (23 February 1919 – 7 April 2013) was a British hereditary peer, decorated Royal Navy officer, solicitor, and heritage figure. From 1978 to 2003, he was custodian of the family seat of St Michael's Mount in Cornwall.
